From Andrew Scott Beals KC SSS Subject Re Drinking and Riding Jerry Hartzler CATS writes In article A Andy Woodward writes I generally find that after two or three decent hits of nitrous, my riding improves enormously Drinking is silly, your breath smells, it costs lots of money and the pigs can detect it with their machines NO works for me, try it And its free just sit behind an old car in a jam, and breathe deeply Only if there is a dentist in the car Otherwise you get NO out the back Me thinks you gots your gases confused What comes out of cars is Carbon Monoxide What comes out of whippits is Nitrous Oxide CO N O